3.    List all invoice items, avoid duplicates.


mysql> select distinct * from INVOICE_ITEM;
+--------+------+----------+
| INV_ID | P_ID | QUANTITY |
+--------+------+----------+
|   1002 |  332 |        4 |
|   1176 |  487 |        5 |
|   1232 |  301 |       50 |
|   1790 |  432 |        2 |
|   1002 |  301 |        2 |
+--------+------+----------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)


mysql> select distinct INV_ID  from INVOICE_ITEM;
+--------+
| INV_ID |
+--------+
|   1002 |
|   1176 |
|   1232 |
|   1790 |
+--------+
4 rows in set (0.02 sec)


